ProtoResult:
. "Let $C = \langle g(t) \rangle$ be a cyclic code in $R_n$ 
   and suppose that $x^n - 1 = g(x) h(x)$. Then $G$ and $H$ are
   generator and parity-check matrices for $C$, respectively. 
   Furthermore, $HG = 0$."
